The Herald Sports Reporter THE Premier Soccer League have announced that the Castle Challenge Cup will be played at Mandava on March 11. The season-opening match will feature four-time champions FC Platinum and Chibuku Super Cup winners Bulawayo Chiefs. The organisers have pegged the cheapest ticket for children in school uniform at US$1 while the rest of the spectators will fork out US$2 for the rest of the ground. The VIP ticket has been set at US$5.